<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;QUICKSILVER VENTURES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Quicksilver Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Silicon Valley, specifically in Saratoga, focusing on acquiring and investing in early-stage, emerging technologies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SILICON VALLEY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Silicon Valley is a region in California known for its high-tech companies and venture capital firms, including Quicksilver Ventures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SARATOGA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Saratoga is a city in Santa Clara County, California, where Quicksilver Ventures is based."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SUPER PLAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Super PLAY, often abbreviated as SP, was a Swedish video game magazine that started in March 1993, initially covering Nintendo games and later expanding to all major consoles and PC games. It had a monthly circulation of 25,000 in 2003."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SWEDEN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sweden is the country where Super PLAY was based and operated."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOBIAS BJARNEBY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tobias Bjarneby was the editor in chief of Super PLAY until November 2004, leaving along with a large segment of the staff to form the new magazine 'Reset'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JOAKIM BENNET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Joakim Bennet succeeded Tommy Rydling as the last editor in chief of Super PLAY in mid-2007."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOMMY RYDLING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Tommy Rydling was the editor in chief of Super PLAY before Joakim Bennet took over in mid-2007."&lt;SEP&gt;"Tommy Rydling was the predecessor of Bennet at GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RESET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Reset is a magazine formed by Tobias Bjarneby and a large segment of the Super PLAY staff after Bjarneby left Super PLAY."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PLAYER 1&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Player 1 is another magazine that merged with Reset to form LEVEL."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEVEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"LEVEL is the result of the merger between Reset and Player 1."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAMEPRO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"GamePro is an American multiplatform video game magazine media company that publishes both online and print content covering the video game industry, hardware, and software."&lt;SEP&gt;"GamePro was an American multiplatform video game magazine media company that published online and print content covering the video game industry, hardware, and software. It featured content on various video game consoles, PC computers, and mobile devices. GamePro Media properties included the magazine and their website. The company was also a part subsidiary of the privately held International Data Group (IDG)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;UNITED STATES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"GamePro is based in the United States."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is a country where Las Vegas and Picasso (restaurant) are located."&lt;SEP&gt;"The United States is the country where Gerald Ford served as President and Vice President, and where the 'drug czar' position is established."&lt;SEP&gt;"United States is the country where the 'war on drugs' was officially declared and where drug policies are implemented."&lt;SEP&gt;"United States is the primary location for the venture capital industry and The Venture Capital Journal (VCJ)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-90530c733fd9b75fb89d03737ba4d5be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26f4d5fee4c1e393eb1a4886ccddc4e9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5cc747d470f8093de4f7eea72bad90a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ed55c5c1b5f070c8b2b666a22793960</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NINTENDO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nintendo is a major console manufacturer that was initially covered by Super PLAY."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAJOR CONSOLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Major consoles refer to the primary gaming platforms that Super PLAY expanded its coverage to in 1995."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PC GAMES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"PC games are a category of video games that Super PLAY started covering in June 2001."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIDEO GAME INDUSTRY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Video game industry encompasses the entire ecosystem of video game development, publishing, and distribution."&lt;SEP&gt;"Video game industry is a concept referring to the broader context in which Bazinama operates."&lt;SEP&gt;"Video game industry is the focus of GamePro's coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIDEO GAME HARDWARE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Video game hardware includes the physical devices used to play video games, such as consoles and computers."&lt;SEP&gt;"Video game hardware is covered by GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIDEO GAME SOFTWARE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Video game software includes the games themselves, which are the software products developed for video game hardware."&lt;SEP&gt;"Video game software is covered by GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VENTURE CAPITAL PORTFOLIOS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Venture capital portfolios are collections of investments in startups and emerging technologies managed by venture capital firms."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EARLY-STAGE, EMERGING TECHNOLOGIES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Early-stage, emerging technologies refer to innovative technologies at the beginning stages of development and commercialization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CORPORATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Corporations are large businesses that Quicksilver Ventures acquires portfolios from."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VENTURE CAPITAL FUNDS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Venture capital funds are investment vehicles that provide funding to startups and emerging companies."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DATA MANAGEMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Data management involves the processes and technologies used to capture, store, secure, and analyze data."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SERVICES AND SECURITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Services and security encompass the provision of IT services and cybersecurity measures."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;STORAGE COMPONENTS AND SYSTEMS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Storage components and systems involve hardware and software solutions for storing and managing data."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ENTERPRISE APPLICATIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Enterprise applications are software solutions designed for business use, such as CRM, ERP, and HR systems."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f58d588c7757e0d408f3d0c94cfbaca3</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BENNET&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bennet succeeded Tommy Rydling in mid-2007 and is associated with GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INTERNATIONAL DATA GROUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"International Data Group (IDG) is an American technology, media, research, event management, and venture capital organization."&lt;SEP&gt;"International Data Group, Inc. (IDG) is a Chinese-owned, American-based media, data, and marketing services and venture capital organization. IDG evolved from International Data Corporation (IDC) which was founded in 1964 in Newtonville, Massachusetts, by Patrick Joseph McGovern. IDC provides market research and advisory services and is now a subsidiary of IDG."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IDC&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"IDC is a market research and advisory services provider that evolved into International Data Group (IDG)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAMEPLAY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"GamePlay is a video game magazine that covers a wide range of gaming platforms, with its first issue released on 28 November 2002 and the final issue in February 2011. The team behind PSX worked on it, and there were plans to create a new version but they were not realized."&lt;SEP&gt;"GamePlay was a Croatian video game magazine that was published on a monthly basis, covering a wide range of gaming platforms including the latest news, previews, reviews, and features. It is considered the successor of 'PSX', with most of the team behind 'PSX' also working on GamePlay. The first issue came out on 28 November 2002."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PATRICK JOSEPH MCGOVERN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Patrick Joseph McGovern founded International Data Corporation (IDC) in 1964 in Newtonville, Massachusetts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEWTONVILLE, MASSACHUSETTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Newtonville, Massachusetts is the founding location of International Data Corporation (IDC)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VENTURE CAPITAL ORGANIZATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Venture capital organization is a type of business that provides financial backing to early-stage companies in exchange for equity. IDG is described as a venture capital organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MEDIA, DATA AND MARKETING SERVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Media, data, and marketing services are the core business areas of International Data Group (IDG)."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MARKET RESEARCH AND ADVISORY SERVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Market research and advisory services are provided by International Data Corporation (IDC), which is now a subsidiary of IDG."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;VIDEO GAME CONSOLES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Video game consoles are covered by GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PC COMPUTERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"PC computers are covered by GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MOBILE DEVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Mobile devices are covered by GamePro magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MAGAZINE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Magazine is a form of periodical publication, and both GamePro and GamePlay are magazines."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WEBSITE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Website is a digital platform for publishing content, and GamePro Media properties include their website."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CROATIA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"GEO"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Croatia is the country where GamePlay magazine is based."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PSX&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"PSX is a predecessor magazine to GamePlay, with a similar focus on video games."&lt;SEP&gt;"PSX is a team behind a gaming platform that works on GamePlay, covering a wide range of gaming platforms and providing the latest news, previews, reviews, and features."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ca848c368a01212f139c69bdcffe3867&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NEXT LEVEL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Next Level is a video game magazine that started in 2012, considered a successor to GamePlay, and also had an accompanying online news site and a forum for discussions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEGA VISIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sega Visions is a video game magazine focusing on Sega video game machines such as Sega Master System, Game Gear, Genesis, and Sega CD. It was initially published by The Communique Group and later by Infotainment World. The magazine had a rather sporadic release schedule and provided content for registered Master System and Genesis owners."&lt;SEP&gt;"Sega Visions was a video game magazine that ran from June/July 1990 to September 1995 with a sporadic release schedule."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;THE COMMUNIQUE GROUP&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The Communique Group was responsible for the initial publication of Sega Visions until 1992."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INFOTAINMENT WORLD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Infotainment World took over the publishing of Sega Visions in 1992 and continued until the end of its lifespan."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;NIC LAVROFF&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Nic Lavroff served as the Editor in Chief for Issues 8 through 17 of Sega Visions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;KURT BUSCH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Kurt Busch served as the Editor in Chief for Issues 18 through 25 of Sega Visions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Kurt Busch was the Editor in Chief for Issues 18 through 25 of a magazine."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEGA MASTER SYSTEM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sega Master System is a video game machine that Sega Visions focused on and provided content for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GAME GEAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Game Gear is a video game machine that Sega Visions focused on and provided content for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GENESIS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Genesis is a video game console mentioned as one of the platforms receiving the premiere issue of Sega Visions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Genesis is a video game machine that Sega Visions focused on and provided content for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEGA CD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sega CD is a video game machine that Sega Visions focused on and provided content for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SEGA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Sega is a video game company that produced various gaming machines such as Sega Master System, Game Gear, Genesis, and Sega CD, and was also involved in publishing Sega Visions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JUNE/JULY 1990&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The premiere issue of Sega Visions was released in June/July 1990 and was sent free to registered Master System and Genesis owners."&lt;SEP&gt;"The premiere issue of Sega Visions was sent free to registered Master System and Genesis owners in June/July 1990."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REGISTERED MASTER SYSTEM AND GENESIS OWNERS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d1">"These were the recipients of the free premiere issue of Sega Visions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ONLINE NEWS SITE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The magazine had an accompanying online news site that provided additional content and updates."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FORUM FOR DISCUSSIONS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"TECHNOLOGY"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The magazine also had a forum for discussions, allowing readers to engage with each other and the editors."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-7319d51bc39d47f493d747d9294d8c60</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;IDG&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"IDG is an abbreviation for International Data Group, an American technology, media, research, event management, and venture capital organization."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BAZINAMA&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Bazinama is the first video game magazine in Iran, published since 2002 by a group of young people interested in the gaming industry."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AKTUELLER SOFTWARE MARKT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d1">"Aktueller Software Markt (ASM) was a German multi-platform video game magazine published by Tronic Verlag from 1986 to 1995."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-c7d7b3d5384b6b708a6ee027163c840e</data>
</node>
